oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: The "Robert E. Lee," one of the parade floats in the Strawberry Festival Parade in Humboldt, Tennessee.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Float was a replica of the original steamer "Robert E. Lee;" it was built to scale on the chassis of a Greyhound bus at the Greyhound Bus Warehouse, Memphis, Tenn., ca. 1939, for the Cotton Carnival.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Festivals; Strawberry Festival; Parades
